text: Pronoides is a genus of Asian orb-weaver spiders first described by E. Schenkel in 1936. ==Species== it contains six species: *Pronoides applanatus Mi & Peng, 2013 – China *Pronoides brunneus Schenkel, 1936 (type) – Russia (Far East), China, Korea, Japan *Pronoides fusinus Mi & Peng, 2013 – China *Pronoides guoi Mi & Peng, 2013 – China *Pronoides sutaiensis Zhang, Zhang & Zhu, 2010 – China *Pronoides trapezius Mi & Peng, 2013 – China ==References== Category:Araneidae Category:Araneomorphae genera Category:Spiders of Asia
title: Pronoides
